│ THOUGHT: This is getting complex. Let me trace through the actual issue more directly. The problem seems to be that when we have `icmp slt i32 (sext i16 X), (zext i16 Y)`, the SLP vectorizer is trying to    │
│ demote this to compare i16 values directly. But this changes the semantics because:                                                                                                                            │
│ - sext i16 X to i32: preserves sign, so negative values stay negative                                                                                                                                          │
│ - zext i16 Y to i32: zero-extends, so negative values become large positive values                                                                                                                             │
│ - Comparing i16 values directly: both are treated as signed i16 values                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The issue is in the logic that decides when to eliminate extensions. Let me look for where extensions might be eliminated when their source and destination types have the same bitwidth:                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ grep -n -B5 -A5 "BWSz == SrcBWSz" ./llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
